      • APNSProperties

        @Inject
public APNSProperties(@Named(value="PushNotificationProvider.APNS.gateway.host") @Nonnull
                              String gatewayHost,
                              @Named(value="PushNotificationProvider.APNS.gateway.port") @Nonnull
                              Integer gatewayPort,
                              @Named(value="PushNotificationProvider.APNS.feedback.host") @Nonnull
                              String feedbackHost,
                              @Named(value="PushNotificationProvider.APNS.feedback.port") @Nonnull
                              Integer feedbackPort,
                              @Named(value="PushNotificationProvider.APNS.p12KeyStore.path") @Nonnull
                              String p12KeyStorePath,
                              @Named(value="PushNotificationProvider.APNS.p12KeyStore.password") @Nonnull
                              String p12KeyStorePassword,
                              @Named(value="PushNotificationProvider.APNS.maxInstances") @Nonnull
                              Integer maxInstances,
                              @Named(value="PushNotificationProvider.APNS.enabled")
                              boolean enabled)
        Parameters:
        gatewayHost - The host name of the gateway. This can be DNS name or IP number.
        gatewayPort - The port of the gateway. The port number must be in range: [1-65535].
        feedbackHost - The host name of the feedback service. This can be DNS name or IP number.
        feedbackPort - The port of the feedback service. The port number must be in range: [1-65535].
        p12KeyStorePath - The path to the P12 keys tore file.
        p12KeyStorePassword - The password of the P12 key store.
        maxInstances - The number of maximum instances of APNS connection that should be used simultaneously. This should be 0 or greater.
        enabled - When set to true messages should be pushed.
        Throws:
        InvalidPropertyValueException - when the gatewayPort or feedbackPort are out of range and when the maxInstances is less than zero.
